    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-12-28T06:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-12-28T06:30:00-05:00" n="460"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d460">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">756D.5–<gloss target="#t_MSP1"
                    >MSP</gloss>/12–2851: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Indonesia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cochran</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Djakarta</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-12-28T19:00:00+07:30"
                            >December 28, 1951—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>924. Ref <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 846 and <gloss
                        target="#t_Ecato1">Ecato</gloss> circ 165.<note n="1" xml:id="d460fn1"
                        >Latter not printed.</note> Discussed with <gloss target="#t_FonMin1"
                        >FonMin</gloss> Subardjo morn 28th draft note which I left with him eleventh
                    seeking assurances required under <gloss target="#t_MSA1">MSA</gloss> legis.
                    Subardjo promised have draft considered cabinet mtg 29th and let me know results
                    thereof 31st. No problems re amendments addition to those mentioned <gloss
                        target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 846 have yet arisen, but <gloss
                        target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss> will likely find necessary to request
                    change in language JBMA 4 from “Govt of <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss>
                    considers aforementioned econ coop agreement fully effective” to that used in
                        <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> core of Oct 27 (see <gloss
                        target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 660, Oct 31) namely “Govt of Republic of
                        <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> states that econ coop agreement
                    between Govt of Republic of <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> and Govt of
                    United States of America, signed in Djakarta on Oct 16, 1950 has been and will
                    continue to be a binding obligation of Republic of <gloss target="#t_Indo1"
                        >Indo</gloss>, according to its terms pending Parl action”.</p>
                <p>Hope report further after seeing Subardjo 31st.<note n="2" xml:id="d460fn2">On
                        December 31, Ambassador Cochran, in telegram 931 from Djakarta, reported
                        that Foreign Minister Subardjo had been unable to get the draft note
                        regarding <gloss target="#t_MSA1">MSA</gloss> assurances before the Cabinet
                        on December 29 (756D.5–<gloss target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss>/12–3151).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cochran</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
